igence, a Mexican consulting firm focused on Social Innovation for Governments and Enterprises\n\nVictor has always been interested in working with the civil society in order make a social change. Since his time in college, he has participated in the creation and management of two NGO´s; he co-founded ConsensoUno with the primary intention of actively creating awareness in Mexico in the areas of Politics, Education, Culture and Social Responsibility.  \n\nHe also co-founded JOIN, a website that promotes citizen journalism in Mexico in order to create alternatives to the biased mass media that exists in his country. In 2010, JOIN received the World Youth Summit Award in the category of “Pursuit of truth” at the United Nations in New York, for using technology to help achieve the Millennium Development Goals.\n\nVictor holds a masters degree in Politics & Mass Media from the University of Liverpool (UK). As part of his studies, he worked to understand the relationship between mass media and politics in modern democracies, with special reference to Britain.  After completing his masters, he worked for the United Nations Non-Governmental Liaison Service at the New York Headquarters.\n\nPrior to his studies in the United Kingdom, Victor received a bachelor’s degree in Communication Science from the Technological Institute of Monterrey (Mexico).\n\n','2011-07-06 09:08:06','2011-07-17 19:16:49','2011/07/06/02_09_48_133_BalStudio.jpg',0,0,'201.154.199.208','517193883',24548269,12,'Art to the people!','jTDpzVd5IA','vhcelaya',NULL,'24548269-SIRUk0uviTiKmCgyVKQ2poRPvKWZB4ysN8swnqhVc','fWuJJ1nNFGvhBkG8OhIbqXq5Vm6sVcm2RTLvWgz74',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(600,'Ricardo.Celaya@sbs.ox.ac.uk','','rcPICNIC11','Ricardo','Celaya',0,'','Co-founder ARTO – Art Beyond Museums / www.arto.mx\r\nCo-founder PIECE - Business & Social Development Intelligence / www.piece-bsdi.com \r\nCo-Founder JOIN / www.join.org.mx \r\n\r\nRicardo is a young Mexican entrepreneur always looking for innovative ways to create a positive impact in the society. \r\n\r\nPassionate about music, arts, business and politics, Ricardo has started different creative ventures throughout his career. In 2009, he cofounded ARTO – Art Beyond Museums, a creative agency which aim is to take back ART TO THE PEOPLE. Using the arts as a disruptive element in society, ARTO’s intention is to create large-scale change in the world.\r\n\r\nBack in 2005, eager to implement positive changes in his country, Ricardo cofounded ConsensoUno, a non-profit organization committed to fostering a culture of citizen responsibility in Mexican youth. Two years later, he also co-founded JOIN, a web-based citizen journalism platform that works as a channel of communication for young Mexicans to give their opinion or propose solutions to different challenges in the country. In 2010, JOIN received the World Youth Summit Award in the category of “Pursuit of truth” at the United Nations in New York, for using technology to help achieve the Millennium Development Goals.\r\n\r\nMore recently, Ricardo co-founded PIECE – Business and Social Development Intelligence, a Mexican consulting firm focused on Social Innovation for Governments and Enterprises.\r\n\r\nRicardo holds a Master of Business Administration from the University of Oxford (2011), and holds a Bachelor’s degree in Industrial Engineering from the Technological Institute of Monterrey Mexico (2005). During his studies at Oxford, he served as president of the Social Entrepreneurship Oxford Business Network. In 2010, he was acknowledged as one of the Top 100 entrepreneurs of the Northeast of Mexico during the Monterrey Venture Capital Conference.\r\n\r\n','2011-07-06 09:20:42','2011-07-07 07:47:32','2011/07/06/02_22_40_588_RicardoCelaya.jpg',0,0,'94.185.130.126','',NULL,6,'Art to the people!',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(601,'dennis@sae.nl','','igloored87','Dennis','Beentjes',0,'',NULL,'2011-07-06 11:06:36','2011-07-06 11:07:30',NULL,0,1,NULL,'10000