s. Money talks but it is not the only factor that makes a business successful',1,'2011-06-11 07:19:33','2011-07-21 09:06:45','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(45,112,13,'Video','Page One seems to be a very interesting documentary about a year inside the The New York Times. About traditional media, partially being taken over by new media, about a loss of power in traditional media, etc. Really interesting, would love to see it!\n',0,'2011-06-11 14:53:36','2011-06-11 14:53:36','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(46,139,NULL,NULL,'Prosocial advertising is a new term to me but one that fits perfectly with the ambitions of GreenGraffiti. Mark Woerde has published a book, \"How will advertising heal the world and your business\" available for free at this link where you can down load it for free  http://www.letsheal.org/ \nThanks Franziska for sending me this link! My blanket is already paying off at Picnic!',0,'2011-06-12 07:42:10','2011-06-12 07:42:10','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(47,139,NULL,NULL,'Not to be blatantly tooting our own horns but I just saw this community action that our Italian partners did. This is what GreenGraffiti® is all about, using new media, social media and the community to make a statement. \nThe Italians go to the poles this week and sustainability is not something the current government is supporting so the people have taken their message to the streets!\nhttp://vimeo.com/24761851 ',0,'2011-06-12 10:57:32','2011-06-12 10:57:32','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(48,139,14,'Video','',0,'2011-06-12 10:58:32','2011-06-12 10:58:32','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(49,87,15,'Video','Love the new Greenpeace Campaign - Facebook: Unfriend coal ',0,'2011-06-12 12:46:12','2011-06-12 12:46:12','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(50,108,13,'Link','Architecture seems to be one of the important themes of this year\'s PICNIC . The artist Pablo Bronstein explores this in his new show just opened at the Institiute of Contemporary Arts in London . Check it out and if you are in London it really is worth a visit. 