 19:26:02','2011-07-14 19:26:02','Member',94,NULL,NULL,NULL),(152,46,146,'Photo','Wow! It is so incredible amazing to see all the beautiful contributions to the project. Some of them have been shared already and a brand new batch is coming soon! Amazing!',0,'2011-07-14 19:41:54','2011-07-14 19:41:54','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(153,78,NULL,NULL,'Im hoping to return this year to PICNIC in the new venue to help with the media exploration and send out the vibes of whats going on and record each element so everyone can further enjoy the experience. I loved it last year and am positively vibrant about it this year!',0,'2011-07-15 12:55:04','2011-07-15 12:55:04','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(155,188,25,'Video','Intoxica = Organic',1,'2011-07-15 22:05:56','2011-07-15 22:05:56','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(156,188,26,'Video','Creatives don\'t go to the supermarket...',1,'2011-07-15 22:08:09','2011-07-15 22:08:09','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(157,188,27,'Video','How does it feel to be famous?',1,'2011-07-15 22:11:12','2011-07-15 22:11:12','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(159,188,28,'Video','Only chickens run from the unknown...',1,'2011-07-15 22:46:58','2011-07-15 22:46:58','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(160,661,NULL,NULL,'I wonder what fabulous things can be achieved still by creating effective apps to bring people together in 1st life.',1,'2011-07-16 14:05:21','2011-07-16 14:05:21','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(161,510,37,'Link','The rainbow moon ... why do I think plenty have seen the Moon in this way before NASA colorized it for scientific purposes. :-)',1,'2011-07-16 17:37:08','2011-07-16 17:37:08','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(162,247,NULL,NULL,'Wireless internet gains popularity very fast in the world, who wins the most market share with media investors  ..? apple or blackberry... \n\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bVO8o_PKvVg\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hylHrudxDdk&feature=related',1,'2011-07-18 09:45:52','2011-07-18 09:45:52','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(163,669,NULL,NULL,'The only legitimate use of technology is to improve our lives. Very excited about the Internet of Things, showcased via the Smart City.',1,'2011-07-18 12:51:19','2011-07-18 12:51:19','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(164,510,38,'Link','Unlike Us: Understanding Social Media Monopolies and their Alternatives is a great  proposal to establish a research network of artists, designers, scholars, activists and programmers who work on ‘alternatives in social media’  Attribution - Wired Magazine; Bruce Sterling\'s Blog - Beyond the Beyond ... well worth reading...what do you think about this proposal?',1,'2011-07-18 15:30:35','2011-07-18 15:30:35','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(165,663,151,'Photo','Just posting that I made the exhibition: Hipstamatic, retropictures with your iPhoneapp in Kunsthal Rotterdam (-28 Aug 2011) is about the iPhone App which transforms your phone into a vintage camera Numerous pictures are being uploaded onto Facebook, Flickr and Twitter. We combined work of profesional photographs like Vincent Mentzel with photos uploaded in our Flickrgroep Hipstamatic Nederland. \r\nPlease keep me posted for similar initiatives!\r\n',1,'2011-07-18 21:16:23','2011-07-18 21:16:23','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(166,673,NULL,NULL,'Google is cool, is that enough?',1,'2011-07-19 02:20:54','2011-07-19 02:20:54','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(167,247,NULL,NULL,'advertisement on facebook , price for placing ads went up with 75%!, it\'s becoming a sellers market for zuckerberg',1,'2011-07-19 08:17:18','2011-07-19 08:17:18','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(168,676,NULL,NULL,'what are the new roles, crafts and jobs that wil arise out of the new web 2.0/3.0. How will existing ICT companies deal with that',1,'2011-07-19 08:52:57','2011-07-19 08:52:57','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(171,499,41,'Link','The 9th Cultural Typhoon - this weekend (2011/7/23-24) in Kobe, at the Conference on Art and Art Projects (CAP)- Studio Y3. This is an international conference of activists, artists, scholars and cultural producers of all kinds.\n\nCheck out the agenda on the Cultural Typhoon site and follow our studio at the CAP site: http://www.cap-kobe.com/studio_y3/\nI\'ll be blogging on the event from the Y3 site beginning Sunday, the 24th. Also, I\'ll be working the kitchen under the skillful direction of Hiroshi Nakagawa.',1,'2011-07-19 12:02:29','2011-07-19 12:02:29','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(172,677,NULL,NULL,'Don\'t forget to pre-book on Sounddropper.com',1,'2011-07-19 14:59:13','2011-07-19 14:59:13','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(173,668,153,'Photo','I want to turn the conventional wisdom about design for aging on its head.',1,'2011-07-19 16:20:23','2011-07-19 16:20:23','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(174,641,NULL,NULL,'I am finishing a unique prefab timberframe structure in old recycled oak. It will go to a jobsite end September. Can place it at the 2011 PICNIC festival Amsterdam \'inside\'. Like to promote my concept of raw and pure dwellings! Hello PICNIC organizers .. Will donate this structure in exchange for exposure. Who wants to join ?',1,'2011-07-19 17:13:25','2011-07-19 17:13:25','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(175,580,42,'Link','A little video from our friends @ Journey of Action.',1,'2011-07-19 20:55:05','2011-07-19 20:55:05','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(176,259,43,'Link','Hey Martine\nThanks for the add - i\'m bringing disposable cameras because i run a little community around disposable photography - http://disposablememoryproject.org, and had a great response the last time i brought a handful to amsterdam. i\'m 100% digital in my day job, so i tend to be a little more analogue in my spare time :)\nLook forward to seeing you at Picnic!',1,'2011-07-20 07:25:36','2011-07-20 07:25:36','Member',47,NULL,NULL,NULL),(177,687,NULL,NULL,'Hello people! See you at the marketplace @Picnic festival 2011!',1,'2011-07-20 07:27:04','2011-07-20 07:27:04','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(178,259,NULL,NULL,'hello franziska - thanks for the add.. the blanket is filling up nicely :)',1,'2011-07-20 07:27:16','2011-07-20 07:27:16','Member',87,NULL,NULL,NULL),(179,693,154,'Photo','I think you might want to explain more about the new location for Picnic this year..that\'s its a cool vibrant revitalised docklands area on the North side o f Amsterdam. You can get there on one of the regular free ferries that leave Central Station. ',1,'2011-07-20 11:24:55','2011-07-20 11:24:55','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(180,693,155,'Photo','NDSM seems to be organising all kinds of events, some which seem to overlap with Picnic. What do you hope makes PICNIC special? Personally, I hope it will generate ideas and actions that will make difference in society. The days of Powerpoint festivals and TED copies are drawing to a close.',1,'2011-07-20 11:40:19','2011-07-20 11:40:19','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(181,693,156,'Photo','There was an excellent, unique Electric Car rally organised in Amsterdam on June 5th. Are there any plans to involve those with hardware innovations in this years Picnic? ',1,'2011-07-20 11:43:24','2011-07-20 11:43:24','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(182,139,29,'Video','GreenAdsBlue is a water foundation targeting the communications industry. We have developed a concept we call \"the Droppelganger\". We hope that creatives, creative agencies and media provider will join us by providing their services to help us promote this water foundation. Here is a video that was made for us by ClipForce as an entry into the YouTube NGO challenge.',1,'2011-07-20 14:01:31','2011-07-20 14:01:31','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(183,510,44,'Link','Hackerspaces, Techshops, Fablabs and co-working spaces are set to change the way we work, manufacturer, create and learn. In the new Urban landscape, these shops will hopefully become as common as coffee bistros are today.  the Link Below is to an article that describes what a few folk in England are doing to further this adoption along.  Check it out and what are your thoughts on the new Urban factory - the place where you live.',1,'2011-07-20 15:11:21','2011-07-20 15:11:21','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(184,139,30,'Video','People often talk about GreenGraffiti® being something new. It is not. It actually uses and old form of street art. What makes it innovative is how we brought together several existing ideas in a new way. \nI was sent this video today which pretty much sums up our view of innovation.',1,'2011-07-21 08:29:53','2011-07-21 08:29:53','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(186,624,45,'Link','Has everyone seen this: www.wemisseyou.de\nListen carefully in the end, there\'s a very funny comment in the background.',1,'2011-07-21 10:49:32','2011-07-21 10:49:32','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(187,624,NULL,NULL,'Evident will be present on the PICNIC Marketplace providing a unique chance to escape from the city and reflect on URBAN Nature. ',1,'2011-07-21 11:17:18','2011-07-21 11:17:18','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
