INSERT INTO `wall_posts` VALUES (3,33,8,'I didn\'t really notice the tags/themes to the far right... Also maybe restrict themes to a pulldown menu?','2011-05-20 08:35:44','2011-05-20 08:35:44',NULL,NULL),(4,2,8,'Hi Todd. Please ignore this! Just testing! Also, the Club area is about to change a lot today based in feedback from Marcel. Also the emails you get will look a lot better.','2011-05-20 08:37:37','2011-05-20 08:37:37',NULL,NULL),(5,33,8,'No problem. I\'m just testing too! But will get out of here now then...','2011-05-20 08:39:24','2011-05-20 08:39:24',NULL,NULL),(6,2,8,'Things will change a lot here by the end of today. Thanks for playing!','2011-05-20 08:59:09','2011-05-20 08:59:09',NULL,NULL),(7,7,13,'Love it','2011-05-25 15:46:50','2011-05-25 15:46:50',NULL,NULL),(8,5,13,'Haha brilliant!','2011-05-26 08:54:32','2011-05-26 08:54:32',NULL,NULL),(9,2,16,'Todd that\'s awesome. I had no idea you did this kinda stuff. Very inspiring.','2011-06-01 20:28:05','2011-06-01 20:28:05',NULL,NULL),(10,2,20,'Stop staring and get your stuff done! ;)','2011-06-03 18:58:27','2011-06-03 18:58:27',NULL,NULL),(11,11,13,'LOL!!','2011-06-07 20:32:42','2011-06-07 20:32:42',NULL,NULL),(12,11,20,'thank you Rich. Completely Zen again after watching this. \nBTW, what is the biggest tank in the world?','2011-06-07 20:38:13','2011-06-07 20:38:13',NULL,NULL),(13,2,24,'Works fine... :-)','2011-06-07 22:21:07','2011-06-07 22:21:07',NULL,NULL),(14,4,20,'Glad it chilled you out Kitty! Apparently the largest tank in the world is in Atlanta, Georgia, according to this blog post http://www.touropia.com/largest-aquariums-in-the-world/','2011-06-08 09:52:51','2011-06-08 09:52:51',NULL,NULL),(15,98,26,'Hi Franziska, I was lucky there was still a free spot on your blanket. Cup of tea?  ','2011-06-08 19:56:07','2011-06-08 19:56:07',NULL,NULL),(16,87,26,'always ;) reminder: need to buy a bigger blanket! ;)','2011-06-08 21:57:19','2011-06-08 21:57:19',NULL,NULL),(17,87,30,'that\'s nice!','2011-06-09 11:06:59','2011-06-09 11:06:59',NULL,NULL),(18,108,29,'Nowhere to hide !','2011-06-09 14:04:22','2011-06-09 14:04:22',NULL,NULL),(19,108,31,'You sure will - already ticketed and ready to help you in any way. Can you fix it for me to say hello to the latest bunch of Knowmads? I am already plotting with Arne Hendriks to build a dance floor BarrysLounge stylee !','2011-06-10 15:50:05','2011-06-10 15:50:05',NULL,NULL),(20,87,31,'will do, will do! can\'t wait to dance with you! but who is Arne Hendriks? (did I miss something??)','2011-06-10 16:06:51','2011-06-10 16:06:51',NULL,NULL),(21,108,31,'I\'ll introduce you on Facebook then you can find out for yourself ... are you planning any visits to London before PICNIC ... Hope so ! Sx','2011-06-10 23:42:58','2011-06-10 23:42:58',NULL,NULL),(22,33,16,'Thanks Andy. It was an amazing experience.','2011-06-11 00:23:09','2011-06-11 00:23:09',NULL,NULL),(23,132,38,'Good idea!!! On your blanket?','2011-06-11 08:42:34','2011-06-11 08:42:34',NULL,NULL),(24,87,43,'Hey Jim, nice meeting you and having you on my blanket. I love what you are writing here and just want to make you aware of \"How Advertising Will Heal the World and Your Business\" by Lemz\'s Mark Woerde. Don\'t know if you know the book already but if not, have a look and download it (for free) via http://www.letsheal.org/ If yes, nevermind... ','2011-06-11 09:02:16','2011-06-11 09:02:16',NULL,NULL),(25,139,43,'Hi Franziska,\nThanks so much for this insight. I have just downloaded the book and will spend a few quiet hours reading it. Great to see that others share the opinion that advertising can be a solution and not just a necessary evil. Picnic is already working for me. THANK YOU!!!','2011-06-11 09:27:04','2011-06-11 09:27:04',NULL,NULL),(26,108,51,'Come to Picnic and inspire others like you have inspired me !','2011-06-13 22:29:18','2011-06-13 22:29:18',NULL,NULL),(27,126,43,'Hi Jim. For a perspective on things south of the equator, you should check out two Sydney companies run by friends of mine: Digital Eskimo and the Republic of Everyone. They are both heavily involved in sustainable communications, ROE are more advertising based, whereas DE are more into service and interaction design. ','2011-06-14 01:58:21','2011-06-14 01:58:21',NULL,NULL),(28,139,43,'Thanks so much for the tip Kimberley. I will have a look at their companies. Greatly appreciated.','2011-06-14 06:00:08','2011-06-14 06:00:08',NULL,NULL),(29,126,18,'I went to the Doors conference in 2000 and loved it. I saw lots of parallels when reading about Picnic: a wide variety of thought makers, future-focussed, sustainably thinking, multi-disciplinary, world improving.... ','2011-06-14 06:53:06','2011-06-14 06:53:06',NULL,NULL),(30,108,55,'When were you at Nokia ? Do you know the fabulous Pria ? Should we get her along to PICNIC ?','2011-06-14 13:15:56','2011-06-14 13:15:56',NULL,NULL),(31,108,26,'Until Franziska gets a bigger blanket ... come and sit on mine !','2011-06-14 14:17:43','2011-06-14 14:17:43',NULL,NULL),(32,108,35,'Are you coming to PICNIC to share ideas with us ? Hope so !','2011-06-14 14:36:37','2011-06-14 14:36:37',NULL,NULL),(33,198,59,'Hello, Sydney! Yes I am planning on actually going, though i\'ve not got my ticket yet. Dan Douglas I used to work with at de-construct. I\'ll give him a prod, see if he\'s around. How do you know the Douglas?','2011-06-14 23:12:36','2011-06-14 23:12:36',NULL,NULL),(34,108,59,'I know all the best people ! He knows all the best accountants !','2011-06-14 23:16:52','2011-06-14 23:16:52',NULL,NULL),(35,204,61,'Sorry to be a pedant, but actually cork is much greener. It\'s a secondary forestry product, and the cork forests of southern spain / portugal are the last habitat of the incredibly endangered Iberian Lynx, the only big cat native to Europe. There\'s an argument that screw caps improve the taste, but its a personal thing. \n\nhttp://www.livepositivelycollective.com/dynamic/live_positively/weve-been-inspired-by-put-a-cork-in-it/','2011-06-15 14:22:17','2011-06-15 14:22:17',NULL,NULL),(36,108,61,'You\'re not a pedant ! It\'s to learn stuff like that is why I go to Picnic !I\'ll bring two bottles and we will compare and contrast !','2011-06-15 15:28:16','2011-06-15 15:28:16',NULL,NULL),(37,108,38,'Hi Maartje , I am so looking forward to Picnic and do hope I will see you there ... You are of course always welcome on my blanket ! S x','2011-06-17 21:50:28','2011-06-17 21:50:28',NULL,NULL),(38,108,62,'Very beautiful ... but here is a green wall with a purpose \nhttp://www.guardian.co.uk/global-development/2011/feb/25/great-green-wall-sahel-desertification','2011-06-17 22:34:08','2011-06-17 22:34:08',NULL,NULL),(39,87,41,'Syd, this is a cool initiative. Want to know more!! We need a Skype call! Pronto!','2011-06-18 23:25:10','2011-06-18 23:25:10',NULL,NULL),(40,108,67,'So will this be an option for accommodation at this year\'s Picnic? Hope so !','2011-06-19 22:37:37','2011-06-19 22:37:37',NULL,NULL),(41,126,55,'Yes, I know the fabulous Pria. She was doing some excellent work there. Yes, she should definitely come along to Picnic. ','2011-06-20 05:06:13','2011-06-20 05:06:13',NULL,NULL),(42,108,55,'On the case !','2011-06-20 06:03:27','2011-06-20 06:03:27',NULL,NULL),(43,11,67,'haha, me too. But it is a bit pricy.... ','2011-06-20 08:18:08','2011-06-20 08:18:08',NULL,NULL),(44,11,58,'Should check with our PR&Communications manager Liz Keel! Her self baked muffins are divine.......','2011-06-20 08:20:55','2011-06-20 08:20:55',NULL,NULL),(45,239,35,'Im from brazil too. i love to share ideas in picnic with you.','2011-06-21 16:56:51','2011-06-21 16:56:51',NULL,NULL),(46,239,24,'Works in brazil too, lol.','2011-06-21 17:01:21','2011-06-21 17:01:21',NULL,NULL),(47,108,51,'Yay ! You\'re coming ! ','2011-06-21 21:45:50','2011-06-21 21:45:50',NULL,NULL),(48,259,72,'i\'m all about the worms...','2011-06-24 15:57:04','2011-06-24 15:57:04',NULL,NULL),(49,108,72,'Must have something to do with Dan D ... get him along too !','2011-06-24 16:26:04','2011-06-24 16:26:04',NULL,NULL),(50,350,78,'Looking for Collaborators world-wide .....','2011-06-28 15:24:38','2011-06-28 15:24:38',NULL,NULL),(51,126,83,'Birdsville. Wow. That really is in the middle of Australia. ','2011-06-29 01:19:53','2011-06-29 01:19:53',NULL,NULL),(52,60,84,'I do! \n\nhttp://www.flickr.com/photos/gchicco/5311875381/in/photostream\n\nhttp://www.flickr.com/photos/gchicco/5191704015/in/photostream\n\nhttp://www.flickr.com/photos/gchicco/4460655780/in/photostream','2011-06-29 06:29:03','2011-06-29 06:29:03',NULL,NULL),(53,126,84,'Ah, I see. I grew up in a small beach town and really prefer to run and walk without shoes. These are a very good city option. ','2011-06-29 23:29:42','2011-06-29 23:29:42',NULL,NULL),(54,522,99,'http://floriesalnot.com/General%20overview1.html','2011-06-30 22:08:42','2011-06-30 22:08:42',NULL,NULL),(55,597,16,'Because of Todd\'s documentary, I taught myself how to play the drums.','2011-07-05 17:30:46','2011-07-05 17:30:46',NULL,NULL),(57,47,112,'Well thanks, so much for me building up points then! I was just curious who you were with all those points, convinced it must be a diehard picnicee :)  \nSo I already found out that we were on the same table last year in the Mongol tent with project dreamschool. Won\'t be too hard then to find you for a cuppa coffee. Cheers, Martine','2011-07-06 09:42:16','2011-07-06 09:42:16',NULL,NULL),(58,607,37,'I too just heard about this a few weeks ago. Would love to hear from anyone who has experience with this platform as well.','2011-07-06 20:04:10','2011-07-06 20:04:10',NULL,NULL),(59,47,20,'maybe you need your PADI as well? :)','2011-07-08 11:14:17','2011-07-08 11:14:17',NULL,NULL),(60,47,20,'Wonderful! So extremely calming under water, lovely','2011-07-08 11:19:39','2011-07-08 11:19:39',NULL,NULL),(62,510,120,'How is the gamification aspects playing out? I like the points / leader board aspects ... reminds me of Evoke, how do others like it','2011-07-08 22:24:56','2011-07-08 22:24:56',NULL,NULL),(63,108,120,'The gamification does rather bring out one\'s inner competitiveness !','2011-07-09 08:55:24','2011-07-09 08:55:24',NULL,NULL),(64,510,120,'yes but I like the way it is done here..without anything but points which have no extra meaning...so people like to get them but they do not go overboard to game the system as it happens on some other sites..oh and nice to meet you Sydney :-) ','2011-07-10 01:05:27','2011-07-10 01:05:27',NULL,NULL),(65,580,18,'An interesting question to ponder is the role of renewables in developing countries. Ironically, these countries are usually rich in natural resources. However, plagued by social problems most of the money has to go to solving these more pressing issues. The solution, I believe, is to involve all sectores of the economy: (i) private, (ii) public, (iii) social.','2011-07-12 01:44:10','2011-07-12 01:44:10',NULL,NULL),(66,2,120,'Hi Kevin. Maybe we could add Google+ integration if it\'s a popular request. But at the moment that are other priorities.','2011-07-12 17:46:43','2011-07-12 17:46:43',NULL,NULL),(67,2,125,'Hi Sydney. I\'m not sure if this message is directed at me, or all the dwellers on your blanket?','2011-07-12 18:02:19','2011-07-12 18:02:19',NULL,NULL),(68,108,75,'Loving the new \"Festival Updates\" bit up above ... and so pleased Bart has won a day ticket but he deserves a Passe Par Tout ticket as he made so many valuable contributions to PICNIC last year !','2011-07-12 18:04:29','2011-07-12 18:04:29',NULL,NULL),(69,2,75,'Thanks Sydney. Did you find the  \"Festival Updates\"  easy to find? Does it work as you expected?','2011-07-12 18:10:14','2011-07-12 18:10:14',NULL,NULL),(70,108,75,'The Festival Updates bit just sort of sprung out at me in a typical delightful PICNIC stylee surprise intervention sort of way !  I didn\'t go looking for it !','2011-07-12 18:19:31','2011-07-12 18:19:31',NULL,NULL),(71,108,125,'No ! I posted it on David De Belleville\'s picnic ( took some finding to work out where but I traced it using the \"Bootcamp\" tag ! ) ... and Blankets are for sitting on .... I am a sociable kind of guy !','2011-07-12 18:25:18','2011-07-12 18:25:18',NULL,NULL),(72,112,75,'Haha, Sydney, you are really flattering me! I am so happy with my Day Ticket!\n\nWhat I notice now: It would be cool if we can mention people in posts, in the way Twitter, Facebook and Google+ do...','2011-07-13 10:23:21','2011-07-13 10:23:21',NULL,NULL),(73,366,136,'Thank you for connecting Sydney! Thanks for the link, very interesting! ;)','2011-07-13 19:06:12','2011-07-13 19:06:12',NULL,NULL),(74,108,91,'How lovely to share this virtual blanket with you and , as you say , let\'s keep the conversations going here until PICNIC .','2011-07-14 01:50:25','2011-07-14 01:50:25',NULL,NULL),(75,108,137,'You want content ! ..... Check out Unpackaged or Enabled By Design or Cockpit Arts or The Knowmads Business School ... The list goes on ! Innovative models with high impact ... That\'s not trite ! Looking forward to meeting you at PICNIC !','2011-07-14 02:45:36','2011-07-14 02:45:36',NULL,NULL),(76,247,140,'Crazy Dutch guy driving to top Alp D\'Huez http://leafplan.nl/english/','2011-07-14 12:01:05','2011-07-14 12:01:05',NULL,NULL),(77,247,137,'social innovation ? meet real people anywhere, instead of track and analyze data on platforms, for the benefit of using it for trends','2011-07-14 12:13:08','2011-07-14 12:13:08',NULL,NULL),(78,108,137,'Exactly ! If you are talking \"Cross Platform\" make sure one of the platforms is Reality and truly analogue !','2011-07-14 12:34:42','2011-07-14 12:34:42',NULL,NULL),(79,510,120,'HI Andy - thanks for the reply- yes, I am sure there are more pressing priorities right now...was still under the influence of the new shiny toy that is Google +... ','2011-07-14 16:05:54','2011-07-14 16:05:54',NULL,NULL),(80,47,143,'They are meant to show who you are and how much activity you show in the club. In time, you will gain more! So keep on exposing your curiousity and knowledge and see what happens :)','2011-07-14 17:05:17','2011-07-14 17:05:17',NULL,NULL),(81,188,134,'Cool!','2011-07-14 17:09:52','2011-07-14 17:09:52',NULL,NULL),(82,580,137,'I agree. Making sure the digital universe has influence over the real world (especially in the decision making process of an organization). \n\nFor example, e-commerce is only so powerful because of the great innovations in wharehousing and logistics. I strongly recommend reading Malcom Gladwell´s article in the New Yorker (attached).\n\nhttp://www.newyorker.com/archive/1999/12/06/1999_12_06_106_TNY_LIBRY_000019693\n\nIn the developing world I consider social innovation being able to give top of the pyramid services and products to bottom of the pyramid population.','2011-07-14 18:07:21','2011-07-14 18:07:21',NULL,NULL),(83,47,145,'Thnx M!!','2011-07-14 19:34:06','2011-07-14 19:34:06',NULL,NULL),(84,247,75,'free augmented realiy app as Aurasma is a much  better idea than google +, to integrate with Picnic, the app is totally free ! (aurasma lite),and promotes any business with Augmented Reality and own made videos or photos by photo recognition.\n\ncheck out this thrilling tool www.aurasma.com  the great way to get more free publicity for Picnic','2011-07-15 10:38:50','2011-07-15 10:38:50',NULL,NULL),(85,510,143,'Hello Martine ... excellent!   Curiosity I have in abundance!  They are also an excellent game mechanic that adds to the experience of participation simply and (hopefully) seamlessly.','2011-07-15 11:42:13','2011-07-15 11:42:13',NULL,NULL),(86,125,35,'Hello Sydney, I don\'t know yet, but I hope so! :)\n\nOi Guilherme, me procura no facebook e vamos conversar... você vai participar dessa edição de 2011?','2011-07-15 19:23:46','2011-07-15 19:23:46',NULL,NULL),(87,188,98,'A COW! produces up to 90kg of methane a year (source .pdf)\nMethane is over 20 times more effective in trapping heat in the atmosphere than carbon dioxide (source)\n90 kg * 2.2 lb/kg = 200 lbs of methane * 20 = 4,000 lbs of CO2 equivalent greenhouse gases.\n','2011-07-15 23:01:07','2011-07-15 23:01:21','2011-07-15 23:01:21',188),(88,188,98,'A cow produces up to 90kg of methane a year \nMethane is over 20 times more effective in trapping heat in the atmosphere than carbon dioxide.\n90 kg * 2.2 lb/kg = 200 lbs of methane * 20 = 4,000 lbs of CO2 equivalent greenhouse gases.\n','2011-07-15 23:02:01','2011-07-16 06:27:20','2011-07-16 06:27:20',188),(89,188,97,'There is a major series of active submarine volcanoes in the Pacific Ocean called the Ring of Fire. Its\' horseshoe-shaped ring extends to roughly 25,000 miles. It consists of more than 450 active and dormant volcanoes, which represents more than 75 percent of the world\'s volcanoes.','2011-07-15 23:07:34','2011-07-16 06:26:50','2011-07-16 06:26:50',188),(90,188,144,'Always in for a party!\nThe Chubbies produced several events for creatives media geeks and freaks alike..\nhttp://www.vimeo.com/chubbynetworks/groups','2011-07-19 20:11:53','2011-07-19 20:11:53',NULL,NULL),(91,188,144,'The eye-catcher of IBC meet mr Vicami!\nhttp://www.vimeo.com/15872224','2011-07-19 20:16:26','2011-07-20 00:30:09',NULL,NULL),(92,580,118,'Hello Kevin. Great video! I look forward to meeting you. It makes me ponder the idea of building new communities properly. This could really be helpful in rural communities of developing countries. We have begun building rural educational centers (we currently operate 70 urban schools) and could use these great tools. Cheers.','2011-07-19 20:53:12','2011-07-19 20:53:12',NULL,NULL),(93,580,17,'So hyped about Picnic! Can we propose a poster?','2011-07-19 20:56:16','2011-07-19 20:56:16',NULL,NULL),(94,188,17,'Hey Marcel,\nYes indeed, we would like to be briefed.','2011-07-20 00:33:06','2011-07-20 00:33:06',NULL,NULL),(95,188,17,'What date is the poster deadline?','2011-07-20 00:34:17','2011-07-20 00:34:27','2011-07-20 00:34:27',188),(96,188,17,'When is the poster deadline?','2011-07-20 00:34:56','2011-07-20 00:34:56',NULL,NULL),(97,87,173,'Yeah! Hope we share the analog one too soon... You will be there for PICNIC, right? ','2011-07-20 11:46:16','2011-07-20 11:46:16',NULL,NULL),(98,108,41,'I am increasingly curious as to whether there will be any participation by the Kinetic Wharf Business Incubator at NDSM at this year\'s PICNIC - I am certain there is much scope for learning and the sharing of ideas ! If there is anyone out there who can shed some light on this it would be much appreciated .','2011-07-20 12:53:45','2011-07-20 12:53:45',NULL,NULL),(99,108,175,'I am all for the analogue and , whilst I am at PICNIC ,  look forward to learning how the Kinetic Wharf Incubator at NDSM is making a difference !','2011-07-20 13:05:14','2011-07-20 13:05:14',NULL,NULL),(100,108,167,'Sorted ! All I need now is an iPhone !','2011-07-20 21:03:51','2011-07-20 21:03:51',NULL,NULL),(101,139,43,'Kimberley Wow Republic of Everyone is enough to make us all envious. Thanks for the lead!','2011-07-21 09:06:45','2011-07-21 09:06:45',NULL,NULL),(102,677,167,'or iPod touch','2011-07-21 10:01:48','2011-07-21 10:01:48',NULL,NULL);
